{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd8db381-d409-4dc5-be2e-e2f236aef063","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_018LmhDwFRgVdZVZFiKdgt7a","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"9663313a-3f9c-4491-922a-cf6bea9955d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. For .NET NativeAOT apps, crash dump collection works differently than regular CoreCLR apps. The key environment variables are:\n   - `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables mini dump collection on crash\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for dump files\n   - `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` - path to createdump tool since it's not in the default location\n\nFor NativeAOT in .NET 8+, crash dump support was added with these same environment variables built into the NativeAOT runtime, though I need to verify the exact mechanism for .NET 11 specifically.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what the user needs to configure in Kubernetes: they'll need to set those environment variables on the container, mount a volume to store the crash dumps, and grant the `SYS_PTRACE` capability so createdump can actually attach to the crashing process.","outputTokens":652,"requestId":"2C4D:1E67:25C07A:2D0FAE:69F94D15"},"id":"70621a16-05d9-4fa7-a388-427a14e33d60","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:51:32.158Z","parentId":"1fd433d0-e490-44e0-9acb-77e693b709a0"}
