{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a64187f1-afa9-4b71-ac48-76dfdda9a1bb","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT:\n\n**Environment variables** to set on the container:\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables automatic dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump (use `2` for heap-only) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp` | Dump file path pattern |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | Custom createdump location |\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: your-app\n    env:\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n      value: \"1\"\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n      value: \"4\"\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n      value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n      value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n    securityContext:\n      capabilities:\n        add:\n        - SYS_PTRACE          # required — createdump uses ptrace\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi         # adjust to your expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is mandatory — `createdump` needs it to read process memory.\n- **`emptyDir`** is fine for transient collection; swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Dump filename tokens: `%e` = executable name, `%p` = PID, `%t` = timestamp.\n- Type `4` (Full) gives the most data but produces the largest files. Use `2` (Heap) for a smaller footprint that still includes managed heap.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9663313a-3f9c-4491-922a-cf6bea9955d8","outputTokens":549,"requestId":"2C4D:1E67:25ED1B:2D4443:69F94D24"},"id":"c3a354d4-b6a1-48ac-88b0-1f3a5a0fa00a","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:51:42.610Z","parentId":"d581a2bf-1377-488e-a32a-c725baea4089"}
